        "plan A/B tests for upgrade screens" .

oc:kn_15ee1198 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When documenting a paywall experiment plan" ;
    oc:directiveContent """## {Category} Experiment: {Name}
- **Hypothesis**: {hypothesis}
- **Control**: {current_state}
- **Variant(s)**: {variants}
- **Primary Metric**: {metric}
- **Secondary Metrics**: {metrics}
- **Minimum Sample**: {sample_size}
- **Duration**: {duration}""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Category",
        "Name",
        "current_state",
        "duration",
        "hypothesis",
        "metric",
        "metrics",
        "sample_size",
        "variants" .

oc:kn_374c61b4 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SuccessIndicator ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When measuring paywall experiment outcomes" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Key metrics for paywall experiments: conversion rate from impression to upgrade, trial start rate, trial-to-paid rate, dismiss rate, and revenue per visitor." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Tracking the full funnel from impression through trial to paid ensures experiments aren't just moving metrics between steps without improving overall conversion." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_6504e9bd a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When starting paywall trigger experiments" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always test hard gate vs. soft gate approaches before optimizing within a single approach, as this is the highest-impact trigger type decision." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The fundamental choice between blocking access and soft prompting determines the entire experiment trajectory and has outsized impact on both conversion and user sentiment." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_7bed5d62 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When planning a comprehensive paywall optimization program" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Paywall experiments should span 7 categories: trigger & timing, design, pricing presentation, copy & messaging, trial & conversion, personalization, and frequency/UX." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Covering all 7 categories ensures no conversion lever is left untested, from when the paywall appears to how users dismiss it." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_b5e4cd86 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When prioritizing which paywall experiments to run" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Sequence experiments from highest-impact structural decisions (trigger type, layout format, trial structure) to lower-impact tactical choices (copy variants, visual elements)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Structural changes have larger effect sizes than copy tweaks, so discovering the right structure first prevents re-running experiments on a suboptimal foundation." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_e4f03544 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When planning and executing paywall optimization experiments" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Identify which of the 7 experiment categories has the highest improvement potential 2. Select a specific sub-category (e.g., 'When to Show' within Trigger & Timing) 3. Choose 2-3 test variants from the catalog 4. Define primary metric and minimum detectable effect 5. Run experiment and analyze results 6. Move to next highest-potential category" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_e963a5f5 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing pricing presentation experiments" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not test pricing display variations without first validating plan structure (number of visible plans, single recommended vs. multi-tier)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Testing price framing on an unvalidated plan structure wastes experiment capacity — structural choices have higher impact than display formatting." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_f084d92c a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When prioritizing personalization experiments" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Personalization experiments should start with usage-based personalization (highlight most-used premium features, show usage stats) before segment-specific variations." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Usage-based personalization requires less segmentation data and infrastructure, making it faster to implement and more broadly applicable." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

